title: Wrong data set result returned when setting an invalid filter expression with 'row[0]'
description: Currently, when attempting to set a filter with the expression 'row[0] equals to 0', the data set is either returning incorrect results or simply returning a null result set.
OB: The data set is returning incorrect results or null result set when setting the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0'.
EB: The data set should either return the correct results or provide an error message indicating that the filter expression is invalid.
SR:
To reproduce this issue: 
1. Set the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' in the data set. 
2. Observe the result set and verify if it is returning incorrect data or a null result set.
